======================================================================
TROPICAL & QUANTUM TOURNAMENTS
kind-pasteur-2026-03-14-S71
======================================================================

======================================================================
PART 1: PERMANENT OF TOURNAMENT ADJACENCY MATRIX
  perm(A) = sum over permutations sigma: prod A[i][sigma(i)]
  This counts CYCLE COVERS, not Hamiltonian paths!
  perm(A) = sum over all cycle covers of T
  Compare: H(T) = sum over Ham PATHS (not cycle covers)
======================================================================

--- n = 3 ---
  H=  1: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  3: perm(A) in [-1]

--- n = 4 ---
  H=  1: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  3: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  5: perm(A) in [1]

--- n = 5 ---
  H=  1: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  3: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  5: perm(A) in [0]
  H=  9: perm(A) in [-1]
  H= 11: perm(A) in [-1]
  H= 13: perm(A) in [-2]
  H= 15: perm(A) in [-3, -2]

======================================================================
PART 2: PERMANENT, DETERMINANT, and H
  perm(A) = unsigned cycle cover count
  det(A) = signed cycle cover count
  H(T) = Hamiltonian path count
  Question: Is there a FORMULA relating them?
======================================================================

--- n = 3 ---
  Correlation(H, perm(A)) = -1.000000
  Correlation(H, det(A)) = 1.000000
  perm(A) + perm(A^op) values: [-2, 0]
  H -> perm(A)-perm(A^op):
    H=  1: diff in [0]
    H=  3: diff in [0]

--- n = 4 ---
  Correlation(H, perm(A)) = 0.894427
  Correlation(H, det(A)) = -0.894427
  perm(A) + perm(A^op) values: [0, 2]
  H -> perm(A)-perm(A^op):
    H=  1: diff in [0]
    H=  3: diff in [0]
    H=  5: diff in [0]

--- n = 5 ---
  Correlation(H, perm(A)) = -0.927173
  Correlation(H, det(A)) = 0.927173
  perm(A) + perm(A^op) values: [-6, -4, -2, 0]
  H -> perm(A)-perm(A^op):
    H=  1: diff in [0]
    H=  3: diff in [0]
    H=  5: diff in [0]
    H=  9: diff in [0]
    H= 11: diff in [0]
    H= 13: diff in [0]
    H= 15: diff in [0]

======================================================================
PART 3: TROPICAL TOURNAMENT — SHORTEST HAMILTONIAN PATH
  Assign weight w(i->j) = 0 if i->j, infinity if j->i
  Then min-weight Ham path = min # 'wrong-direction' arcs = 0
  More interesting: w(i->j) = |i-j| (displacement cost)
  Or: w(i->j) = 1 - T[i][j] (number of backward arcs)
======================================================================

--- n = 4 ---
  H -> min backward arcs in any Ham path:
    H=  1: min_back in [0, 1, 2, 3], mean_back=1.50
    H=  3: min_back in [0, 1, 2], mean_back=1.50
    H=  5: min_back in [0, 1, 2], mean_back=1.50

