  Correlation(H, Kemeny) = 0.863124

======================================================================
PART 5: TOURNAMENT ENTROPY AND INFORMATION CONTENT
  Score entropy: S = -sum (s_i/total) log(s_i/total)
  H-entropy: log2(H) measures 'disorder' of tournament
  Question: Is log2(H) ~ n * score_entropy?
======================================================================

--- n = 5 ---
  Correlation(logH, score_entropy) = 0.933317
  Correlation(logH, score_variance) = -0.969606
  Correlation(logH, c3) = 0.969606
  Correlation(H, score_entropy) = 0.925935
  Correlation(H, score_variance) = -0.973329

  H-maximizer (H=15):
    score_entropy = 2.2464
    score_var = 0.4000
    c3 = 4
    log2(H) = 3.9069
  Max entropy = 2.3219: H in [15]

